c/07-api.md:§Recipes\"\n   445→  milestone: \"M5\"\n   446→  lane: 11\n   447→  status: \"pending\"\n   448→  test: null\n   449→  commit: null\n   450→\n   451→- id: \"CHK-041\"\n   452→  description: \"Recipe seed data: 30+ recipes with ingredients linked to food DB; macros per serving auto-calculated from RecipeIngredient weights\"\n   453→  source: \"spec/01-features.md:§F6\"\n   454→  milestone: \"M5\"\n   455→  lane: 11\n   456→  status: \"pending\"\n   457→  test: null\n   458→  commit: null\n   459→\n   460→- id: \"CHK-042\"\n   461→  description: \"Recipe browser UI (S-COACH-3): grid/list toggle, filter bar (diet type, prep time, calorie range), recipe cards. Recipe detail (S-COACH-4): hero image, macros per serving, serving selector (scales ingredients), ingredients list, step-by-step instructions, 'Log this meal' button → meal slot picker, favorite toggle, custom recipe builder (add food DB items as ingredients, auto-calculate macros). Empty state (no favorites): 'Save recipes you love here' + Browse recipes CTA.\"\n   462→  source: \"spec/04-screens.md:§S-COACH-3\"\n   463→  milestone: \"M5\"\n   464→  lane: 11\n   465→  status: \"pending\"\n   466→  test: null\n   467→  commit: null\n   468→\n   469→# ── M6: PWA & Polish ──────────────────────────────────────────\n   470→\n   471→- id: \"CHK-043\"\n   472→  description: \"Service worker (Workbox/next-pwa): offline read cache for dashboard + journal + recipes, install prompt (Add to Home Screen)\"\n   473→  source: \"spec/08-milestones.md:§Milestone 6\"\n   474→  milestone: \"M6\"\n   475→  lane: 12\n   476→  status: \"pending\"\n   477→  test: null\n   478→  commit: null\n   479→\n   480→- id: \"CHK-044\"\n   481→  description: \"Background sync + Dexie.js offline store: queue log entries while offline, sync to server on reconnect, offline indicator banner when no connection\"\n   482→  source: \"spec/05-tech-stack.md:§Frontend\"\n   483→  milestone: \"M6\"\n   484→  lane: 12\n   485→  status: \"pending\"\n   486→  test: null\n   487→  commit: null\n   488→\n   489→- id: \"CHK-045\"\n   490→  description: \"Push notifications: per-slot meal reminders (configurable schedule from CHK-022 settings), weekly check-in prompt\"\n   491→  source: \"spec/08-milestones.md:§Milestone 6\"\n   492→  milestone: \"M6\"\n   493→  lane: 12\n   494→  status: \"pending\"\n   495→  test: null\n   496→  commit: null\n   497→\n   498→- id: \"CHK-057\"\n   499→  description: \"Email jobs via Nodemailer + SMTP: BullMQ daily-reminder-email job (morning summary of yesterday + today goal) and weekly-summary-email job (weekly progress digest). Distinct from push notifications — email channel.\"\n   500→  source: \"spec/05-tech-stack.md:§Backend\"\n   501→  milestone: \"M6\"\n   502→  lane: 12\n   503→  status: \"pending\"\n   504→  test: null\n   505→  commit: null\n   506→\n   507→- id: \"CHK-046\"\n   508→  description: \"Animations + transitions: page fade (150ms), list stagger-fade (30ms/item), calorie ring fill on mount (0→current, 600ms ease-out), number count animation on kcal updates after logging, toast slide-up (auto-dismiss 3s), bottom sheet spring (cubic-bezier(0.32,0.72,0,1)), milestone celebrations (streak record, goal reached — bounce + confetti). All wrapped in prefers-reduced-motion guard.\"\n   509→  source: \"spec/06-ux-design.md:§Motion & Transitions\"\n   510→  milestone: \"M6\"\n   511→  lane: 13\n   512→  status: \"pending\"\n   513→  test: null\n   514→  commit: null\n   515→\n   516→- id: \"CHK-047\"\n   517→  description: \"Accessibility audit (WCAG AA): min 44×44px tap targets on all interactive elements, keyboard navigation + visible focus rings (2px primary), aria labels on all icon-only buttons, color contrast ≥4.5:1 text / ≥3:1 UI components, no information conveyed by color alone (always text/icon backup), screen reader testing\"\n   518→  source: \"spec/06-ux-design.md:§Accessibility\"\n   519→  milestone: \"M6\"\n   520→  lane: 13\n   521→  status: \"pending\"\n   522→  test: null\n   523→  commit: null\n   524→\n   525→# ── M7: Self-Hosting & Docs ───────────────────────────────────\n   526→\n   527→- id: \"CHK-048\"\n   528→  description: \"Docker Compose production config: multi-stage Next.js build, non-root users, health checks for all services, environment variables documented in .env.example\"\n   529→  source: \"spec/08-milestones.md:§Milestone 7\"\n   530→  milestone: \"M7\"\n   531→  lane: 13\n   532→  status: \"pending\"\n   533→  test: null\n   534→  commit: null\n   535→\n   536→- id: \"CHK-049\"\n   537→  description: \"Project documentation: README with screenshots + quick-start, self-hosting guide (Docker Compose setup, env vars, first run), contributing guide\"\n   538→  source: \"spec/08-milestones.md:§Milestone 7\"\n   539→  milestone: \"M7\"\n   540→  lane: 13\n   541→  status: \"pending\"\n   542→  test: null\n   543→  commit: null\n   544→\n   545→- id: \"CHK-059\"\n   546→  description: \"OpenAPI spec auto-generation: wire Hono + Zod schema types to @hono/zod-openapi, serve GET /api/openapi.json and Swagger UI at /api/docs\"\n   547→  source: \"spec/05-tech-stack.md:§Developer Experience\"\n   548→  milestone: \"M7\"\n   549→  lane: 13\n   550→  status: \"pending\"\n   551→  test: null\n   552→  commit: null\n   553→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bb97f10c-f3e9-4d4d-8c90-eca16b368ef0","uuid":"68f62cf7-78e5-4ae8-9fba-5bc9b63c7c45","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/claude/code/foodadvisor/.forge/checkboxes.yaml","content":"# forge:plan --cycle 1\n# 59 checkboxes — amended + 10 new (CHK-050..059)\n# Gap fixes: GAP-01..31 per review 2026-03-03\n\n# ── M0: Foundation ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n- id: \"CHK-001\"\n  description: \"Scaffold pnpm monorepo with Next.js 15 (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind v4, Hono API routes, Vitest, Playwright\"\n  source: \"spec/05-tech-stack.md:§Stack Decision\"\n  milestone: \"M0\"\n  lane: 1\n  status: \"pending\"\n  test: null\n  commit: null\n\n- id: \"CHK-002\"\n  description: \"Docker Compose dev config: PostgreSQL 16, Redis, MinIO, Ollama (optional), app service with hot-reload\"\n  source: \"spec/05-tech-stack.md:§Infrastructure (Self-hosted)\"\n  milestone: \"M0\"\n  lane: 1\n  status: \"pending\"\n  test: null\n  commit: null\n\n- id: \"CHK-003\"\n  description: \"Drizzle ORM setup + initial migration: User, UserProfile, DailyTargets, Food (with nameTranslations JSONB + micronutrients JSONB), ServingSize, MealEntry, WaterEntry, WeightEntry, ActivityEntry, Exercise, FavoriteRecipes tables\"\n  source: \"spec/02-data-models.md:§Core Models\"\n  milestone: \"M0\"\n  lane: 1\n  status: \"pending\"\n  test: null\n  commit: null\n\n- id: \"CHK-004\"\n  description: \"Better Auth integration: email/password register, login, logout, refresh, forgot/reset password, JWT session middleware\"\n  source: \"spec/07-api.md:§Auth\"\n  milestone: \"M0\"\n  lane: 1\n  status: \"pending\"\n  test: null\n  commit: null\n\n- id: \"CHK-005\"\n  description: \"Design system: Tailwind theme with spec tokens (Primary #16A34A, Accent #F59E0B, macro colors: Protein #3B82F6 / Carbs #A855F7 / Fat #EF4444 / Fiber #10B981), Inter variable font, 4px spacing grid, border-radii (sm:6px md:12px lg:16px xl:24px full:9999px), shadcn/ui base components (Button, Input, Card, Dialog, Sheet, Toast). NO traffic-light food classification.\"\n  source: \"spec/06-ux-design.md:§Design System\"\n  milestone: \"M0\"\n  lane: 2\n  status: \"pending\"\n  test: null\n  commit: null\n\n- id: \"CHK-006\"\n  description: \"App shell: responsive layout — bottom tab bar 5 items