{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013yP8SBECUVk5va5GCTQTES","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# API Specification\n     2→\n     3→## Conventions\n     4→\n     5→- Base path: `/api/v1`\n     6→- Auth: Bearer token (JWT) in `Authorization` header\n     7→- Dates: ISO 8601 (`2025-03-02`)\n     8→- Weights: always grams (decimal)\n     9→- Calories: always kcal (decimal)\n    10→- Errors: `{ error: string, code: string, details?: object }`\n    11→\n    12→---\n    13→\n    14→## Auth\n    15→\n    16→```\n    17→POST   /api/auth/register        Body: {email, password, name?}\n    18→POST   /api/auth/login           Body: {email, password}\n    19→POST   /api/auth/logout\n    20→POST   /api/auth/refresh\n    21→POST   /api/auth/forgot-password Body: {email}\n    22→POST   /api/auth/reset-password  Body: {token, password}\n    23→```\n    24→\n    25→---\n    26→\n    27→## User Profile\n    28→\n    29→```\n    30→GET    /api/v1/profile           → UserProfile + DailyTargets\n    31→PUT    /api/v1/profile           Body: Partial<UserProfile>\n    32→POST   /api/v1/profile/recalculate-targets  → new DailyTargets\n    33→```\n    34→\n    35→---\n    36→\n    37→## Food Database\n    38→\n    39→```\n    40→GET    /api/v1/foods/search      ?q=chicken&limit=20&offset=0\n    41→GET    /api/v1/foods/:id\n    42→GET    /api/v1/foods/barcode/:barcode\n    43→POST   /api/v1/foods             Body: CreateFoodDto   (user custom food)\n    44→PUT    /api/v1/foods/:id         (own foods only)\n    45→DELETE /api/v1/foods/:id         (own foods only)\n    46→\n    47→GET    /api/v1/foods/recent      → last 20 logged foods for user\n    48→GET    /api/v1/foods/favorites   → user favorites\n    49→POST   /api/v1/foods/:id/favorite\n    50→DELETE /api/v1/foods/:id/favorite\n    51→```\n    52→\n    53→### Search Response\n    54→\n    55→```typescript\n    56→{\n    57→  items: FoodSearchItem[]\n    58→  total: number\n    59→  source: \"local\" | \"usda\" | \"openfoodfacts\"\n    60→}\n    61→\n    62→FoodSearchItem {\n    63→  id: string\n    64→  name: string\n    65→  brandName: string | null\n    66→  caloriesPer100g: number\n    67→  proteinPer100g: number\n    68→  carbsPer100g: number\n    69→  fatPer100g: number\n    70→  servingSizes: ServingSize[]\n    71→  source: string\n    72→}\n    73→```\n    74→\n    75→---\n    76→\n    77→## Meal Logging\n    78→\n    79→```\n    80→GET    /api/v1/logs/:date               → DailyLog (all entries for date)\n    81→POST   /api/v1/logs/:date/meals         Body: CreateMealEntryDto\n    82→PUT    /api/v1/logs/meals/:entryId      Body: UpdateMealEntryDto\n    83→DELETE /api/v1/logs/meals/:entryId\n    84→\n    85→POST   /api/v1/logs/:date/water         Body: {amountMl: number}\n    86→DELETE /api/v1/logs/water/:entryId\n    87→\n    88→POST   /api/v1/logs/:date/weight        Body: {weightKg: number, note?: string}\n    89→PUT    /api/v1/logs/weight/:entryId\n    90→DELETE /api/v1/logs/weight/:entryId\n    91→\n    92→POST   /api/v1/logs/:date/activities    Body: CreateActivityEntryDto\n    93→PUT    /api/v1/logs/activities/:entryId\n    94→DELETE /api/v1/logs/activities/:entryId\n    95→```\n    96→\n    97→### Daily Log Response\n    98→\n    99→```typescript\n   100→DailyLog {\n   101→  date: string\n   102→  summary: {\n   103→    caloriesConsumed: number\n   104→    caloriesTarget: number\n   105→    caloriesBurned: number\n   106→    proteinG: number\n   107→    carbsG: number\n   108→    fatG: number\n   109→    fiberG: number\n   110→    waterMl: number\n   111→    waterTargetMl: number\n   112→    weightKg: number | null\n   113→  }\n   114→  meals: {\n   115→    slot: MealSlot\n   116→    entries: MealEntry[]\n   117→    totalKcal: number\n   118→  }[]\n   119→  water: WaterEntry[]\n   120→  activities: ActivityEntry[]\n   121→}\n   122→```\n   123→\n   124→---\n   125→\n   126→## Photo Recognition\n   127→\n   128→```\n   129→POST   /api/v1/recognize/photo\n   130→  Body: multipart/form-data { image: File }\n   131→  → { jobId: string }\n   132→\n   133→# Client subscribes to SSE stream — no polling\n   134→GET    /api/v1/recognize/photo/:jobId/stream   (text/event-stream)\n   135→  Events:\n   136→    data: { status: \"processing\" }\n   137→    data: { status: \"done\", items: RecognizedItem[] }\n   138→    data: { status: \"failed\", error: string }\n   139→\n   140→# Fallback for environments without SSE support\n   141→GET    /api/v1/recognize/photo/:jobId\n   142→  → { status: \"pending\" | \"done\" | \"failed\", items?: RecognizedItem[], error?: string }\n   143→\n   144→RecognizedItem { name: string, weightG: number, confidence: number, food?: FoodSearchItem }\n   145→```\n   146→\n   147→---\n   148→\n   149→## Analytics\n   150→\n   151→```\n   152→GET    /api/v1/analytics/summary?from=2025-01-01&to=2025-03-01\n   153→  → {\n   154→      days: DailySummary[]        // one per day in range\n   155→      averages: {...}\n   156→      streaks: { current: number, best: number }\n   157→    }\n   158→\n   159→GET    /api/v1/analytics/nutrients?from=...&to=...\n   160→  → per-day nutrient totals\n   161→\n   162→GET    /api/v1/analytics/weight?from=...&to=...\n   163→  → weight entries + trend line\n   164→\n   165→GET    /api/v1/analytics/foods/top?from=...&to=...&limit=10\n   166→  → most logged foods in period\n   167→```\n   168→\n   169→---\n   170→\n   171→## Recipes\n   172→\n   173→```\n   174→GET    /api/v1/recipes           ?diet=vegan&maxTime=30&maxCalories=600&q=chicken\n   175→GET    /api/v1/recipes/:id\n   176→POST   /api/v1/recipes           Body: CreateRecipeDto  (user recipes)\n   177→PUT    /api/v1/recipes/:id       (own or admin)\n   178→DELETE /api/v1/recipes/:id\n   179→\n   180→POST   /api/v1/recipes/:id/favorite\n   181→DELETE /api/v1/recipes/:id/favorite\n   182→GET    /api/v1/recipes/favorites\n   183→\n   184→POST   /api/v1/recipes/:id/log   Body: {date, mealSlot, servings}\n   185→  → creates MealEntry for each ingredient\n   186→```\n   187→\n   188→---\n   189→\n   190→## Educational Content\n   191→\n   192→```\n   193→GET    /api/v1/lessons           ?category=nutrition&limit=20\n   194→GET    /api/v1/lessons/:id\n   195→GET    /api/v1/lessons/today     → today's queued lessons for user\n   196→POST   /api/v1/lessons/:id/complete\n   197→GET    /api/v1/lessons/progress  → { completed: number, total: number, byCategory: {...} }\n   198→```\n   199→\n   200→---\n   201→\n   202→## Exercises\n   203→\n   204→```\n   205→GET    /api/v1/exercises         ?q=running&category=cardio\n   206→GET    /api/v1/exercises/:id\n   207→```\n   208→\n   209→---\n   210→\n   211→## Data Export\n   212→\n   213→```\n   214→GET    /api/v1/export/json       → full user data as JSON\n   215→GET    /api/v1/export/csv        → meal logs as CSV\n   216→```\n   217→\n   218→---\n   219→\n   220→## Error Codes\n   221→\n   222→| Code | HTTP | Description |\n   223→|---|---|---|\n   224→| `unauthorized` | 401 | Missing or invalid token |\n   225→| `forbidden` | 403 | Resource not owned by user |\n   226→| `not_found` | 404 | Resource not found |\n   227→| `validation_error` | 422 | Request body invalid |\n   228→| `barcode_not_found` | 404 | Barcode not in any database |\n   229→| `recognition_failed` | 422 | Photo recognition returned no results |\n   230→| `food_db_unavailable` | 503 | External food DB unreachable |\n   231→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bb97f10c-f3e9-4d4d-8c90-eca16b368ef0","uuid":"a5112252-1f67-42e3-9bff-04c4fc51fd87","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/claude/code/foodadvisor/spec/07-api.md","content":"# API Specification\n\n## Conventions\n\n- Base path: `/api/v1`\n- Auth: Bearer token (JWT) in `Authorization` header\n- Dates: ISO 8601 (`2025-03-02`)\n- Weights: always grams (decimal)\n- Calories: always kcal (decimal)\n- Errors: `{ error: string, code: string, details?: object }`\n\n---\n\n## Auth\n\n```\nPOST   /api/auth/register        Body: {email, password, name?}\nPOST   /api/auth/login           Body: {email, password}\nPOST   /api/auth/logout\nPOST   /api/auth/refresh\nPOST   /api/auth/forgot-password Body: {email}\nPOST   /api/auth/reset-password  Body: {token, password}\n```\n\n---\n\n## User Profile\n\n```\nGET    /api/v1/profile           → UserProfile + DailyTargets\nPUT    /api/v1/profile           Body: Partial<UserProfile>\nPOST   /api/v1/profile/recalculate-targets  → new DailyTargets\n```\n\n---\n\n## Food Database\n\n```\nGET    /api/v1/foods/search      ?q=chicken&limit=20&offset=0\nGET    /api/v1/foods/:id\nGET    /api/v1/foods/barcode/:barcode\nPOST   /api/v1/foods             Body: CreateFoodDto   (user custom food)\nPUT    /api/v1/foods/:id         (own foods only)\nDELETE /api/v1/foods/:id         (own foods only)\n\nGET    /api/v1/foods/recent      → last 20 logged foods for user\nGET    /api/v1/foods/favorites   → user favorites\nPOST   /api/v1/foods/:id/favorite\nDELETE /api/v1/foods/:id/favorite\n```\n\n### Search Response\n\n```typescript\n{\n  items: FoodSearchItem[]\n  total: number\n  source: \"local\" | \"usda\" | \"openfoodfacts\"\n}\n\nFoodSearchItem {\n  id: string\n  name: string\n  brandName: string | null\n  caloriesPer100g: number\n  proteinPer100g: number\n  carbsPer100g: number\n  fatPer100g: number\n  servingSizes: ServingSize[]\n  source: string\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Meal Logging\n\n```\nGET    /api/v1/logs/:date               → DailyLog (all entries for date)\nPOST   /api/v1/logs/:date/meals         Body: CreateMealEntryDto\nPUT    /api/v1/logs/meals/:entryId      Body: UpdateMealEntryDto\nDELETE /api/v1/logs/meals/:entryId\n\nPOST   /api/v1/logs/:date/water         Body: {amountMl: number}\nDELETE /api/v1/logs/water/:entryId\n\nPOST   /api/v1/logs/:date/weight        Body: {weightKg: number, note?: string}\nPUT    /api/v1/logs/weight/:entryId\nDELETE /api/v1/logs/weight/:entryId\n\nPOST   /api/v1/logs/:date/activities    Body: CreateActivityEntryDto\nPUT    /api/v1/logs/activities/:entryId\nDELETE /api/v1/logs/activities/:entryId\n```\n\n### Daily Log Response\n\n```typescript\nDailyLog {\n  date: string\n  summary: {\n    caloriesConsumed: number\n    caloriesTarget: number\n    caloriesBurned: number\n    proteinG: number\n    carbsG: number\n    fatG: number\n    fiberG: number\n    waterMl: number\n    waterTargetMl: number\n    weightKg: number | null\n  }\n  meals: {\n    slot: MealSlot\n    entries: MealEntry[]\n    totalKcal: number\n  }[]\n  water: WaterEntry[]\n  activities: ActivityEntry[]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Photo Recognition\n\n```\nPOST   /api/v1/recognize/photo\n  Body: multipart/form-data { image: File }\n  → { jobId: string }\n\n# Client subscribes to SSE stream — no polling\nGET    /api/v1/recognize/photo/:jobId/stream   (text/event-stream)\n  Events:\n    data: { status: \"processing\" }\n    data: { status: \"done\", items: RecognizedItem[] }\n    data: { status: \"failed\", error: string }\n\n# Fallback for environments without SSE support\nGET    /api/v1/recognize/photo/:jobId\n  → { status: \"pending\" | \"done\" | \"failed\", items?: RecognizedItem[], error?: string }\n\nRecognizedItem { name: string, weightG: number, confidence: number, food?: FoodSearchItem }\n```\n\n---\n\n## Analytics\n\n```\nGET    /api/v1/analytics/summary?from=2025-01-01&to=2025-03-01\n  → {\n      days: DailySummary[]        // one per day in range\n      averages: {...}\n      streaks: { current: number, best: number }\n    }\n\nGET    /api/v1/analytics/nutrients?from=...&to=...\n  → per-day nutrient totals\n\nGET    /api/v1/analytics/weight?from=...&to=...\n  → weight entries + trend line\n\nGET    /api/v1/analytics/foods/top?from=...&to=...&limit=10\n  → most logged foods in period\n```\n\n---\n\n## Recipes\n\n```\nGET    /api/v1/recipes           ?diet=vegan&maxTime=30&maxCalories=600&q=chicken\nGET    /api/v1/recipes/:id\nPOST   /api/v1/recipes           Body: CreateRecipeDto  (user recipes)\nPUT    /api/v1/recipes/:id       (own or admin)\nDELETE /api/v1/recipes/:id\n\nPOST   /api/v1/recipes/:id/favorite\nDELETE /api/v1/recipes/:id/favorite\nGET    /api/v1/recipes/favorites\n\nPOST   /api/v1/recipes/:id/log   Body: {date, mealSlot, servings}\n  → creates MealEntry for each ingredient\n```\n\n---\n\n## Educational Content\n\n```\nGET    /api/v1/lessons           ?category=nutrition&limit=20\nGET    /api/v1/lessons/:id\nGET    /api/v1/lessons/today     → today's queued lessons for user\nPOST   /api/v1/lessons/:id/complete\nGET    /api/v1/lessons/progress  → { completed: number, total: number, byCategory: {...} }\n```\n\n---\n\n## Exercises\n\n```\nGET    /api/v1/exercises         ?q=running&category=cardio\nGET    /api/v1/exercises/:id\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Export\n\n```\nGET    /api/v1/export/json       → full user data as JSON\nGET    /api/v1/export/csv        → meal logs as CSV\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Codes\n\n| Code | HTTP | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `unauthorized` | 401 | Missing or invalid token |\n| `forbidden` | 403 | Resource not owned by user |\n| `not_found` | 404 | Resource not found |\n| `validation_error` | 422 | Request body invalid |\n| `barcode_not_found` | 404 | Barcode not in any database |\n| `recognition_failed` | 422 | Photo recognition returned no results |\n| `food_db_unavailable` | 503 | External food DB unreachable |\n","numLines":231,"startLine":1,"totalLines":231}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FNciXNTFTunGmzjJiAqWdt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Tech Stack\n     2→\n     3→## Guiding Constraints\n     4→\n     5→- Fully open-source (MIT or compatible licenses)\n     6→- Self-hostable via Docker Compose\n     7→- No vendor lock-in on any critical path\n     8→- Web-first, PWA for mobile\n     9→- Food recognition must work without paying per-request (or have a free tier path)\n    10→\n    11→---\n    12→\n    13→## Stack Decision\n    14→\n    15→### Frontend\n    16→\n    17→| Layer | Choice | Rationale |\n    18→|---|---|---|\n    19→| Framework | **Next.js 15** (App Router) | SSR + RSC, great PWA support, large ecosystem |\n    20→| Language | **TypeScript** | Type safety, especially for nutrition math |\n    21→| Styling | **Tailwind CSS v4** | Utility-first, no runtime, good responsive |\n    22→| Component system | **shadcn/ui** (Radix primitives) | Accessible, unstyled, own the code |\n    23→| State management | **Zustand** | Lightweight, no boilerplate |\n    24→| Server state / cache | **TanStack Query** | Async data fetching, offline support |\n    25→| Charts | **Recharts** | React-native, MIT, good for health dashboards |\n    26→| Camera / barcode | **@zxing/library** (barcode) + native `getUserMedia` | Browser-native |\n    27→| Forms | **React Hook Form** + **Zod** | Performant, type-safe validation |\n    28→| Offline / PWA | **Workbox** via next-pwa | Service worker, background sync |\n    29→| Local storage | **Dexie.js** (IndexedDB wrapper) | Offline-first food log |\n    30→\n    31→### Backend\n    32→\n    33→| Layer | Choice | Rationale |\n    34→|---|---|---|\n    35→| Runtime | **Node.js 22 LTS** | Stable, wide hosting support |\n    36→| Framework | **Hono** | Lightweight, edge-ready, fast, typed |\n    37→| API style | **REST + JSON** (OpenAPI spec) | Simple, widely understood |\n    38→| ORM | **Drizzle ORM** | TypeScript-first, lightweight, great migrations |\n    39→| Database | **PostgreSQL 16** | Reliable, JSONB for micronutrients, full-text search |\n    40→| Auth | **Better Auth** | Open-source, self-hosted, OAuth support |\n    41→| File/image storage | **MinIO** (S3-compatible) | Self-hostable object storage |\n    42→| Job queue | **BullMQ** (Redis-backed) | Background jobs: photo analysis, notifications |\n    43→| Email | **Nodemailer** + SMTP | Password reset, self-configured |\n    44→\n    45→### AI / Food Recognition\n    46→\n    47→**Tier 1 (default): LLM Vision API**\n    48→- Use OpenAI GPT-4o Vision or open-alternative (Ollama + LLaVA)\n    49→- Prompt: identify food items and estimate gram weights from photo\n    50→- Self-hosted option: Ollama with `llava` or `moondream2` model\n    51→- Structured output: JSON list of `{name, weightG, confidence}`\n    52→\n    53→**Tier 2: Open Food Facts + USDA for lookup**\n    54→- All barcode / text search backed by Open Food Facts API (free, open)\n    55→- Fallback: USDA FoodData Central API (free API key)\n    56→- Local DB cache: bulk import Open Food Facts dataset (CSV, ~2GB)\n    57→\n    58→**Voice logging**: Web Speech API (browser-native, no backend needed)\n    59→\n    60→**NLP quick-add**: lightweight model or LLM call to parse \"2 eggs and oatmeal 80g\"\n    61→\n    62→### Infrastructure (Self-hosted)\n    63→\n    64→```yaml\n    65→# docker-compose.yml services\n    66→services:\n    67→  app:        # Next.js (frontend + API routes)\n    68→  postgres:   # PostgreSQL 16\n    69→  redis:      # BullMQ + session cache\n    70→  minio:      # Object storage (food images, user photos)\n    71→  ollama:     # Optional: local LLM for photo recognition\n    72→```\n    73→\n    74→### External APIs (all free-tier or open)\n    75→\n    76→| Service | Use | Cost |\n    77→|---|---|---|\n    78→| Open Food Facts | Barcode lookup, food DB | Free, CC BY-SA |\n    79→| USDA FoodData Central | Food nutritional data | Free (API key) |\n    80→| OpenAI / Anthropic | Photo recognition (optional hosted) | Pay-per-use fallback |\n    81→| Ollama (self-hosted) | Photo recognition (fully free) | Free, own hardware |\n    82→\n    83→---\n    84→\n    85→## Architecture Diagram\n    86→\n    87→```\n    88→Browser (PWA)\n    89→  │\n    90→  ├── Service Worker (offline cache, background sync)\n    91→  ├── IndexedDB (local food log, offline entries)\n    92→  │\n    93→  └── HTTPS → Next.js App\n    94→               │\n    95→               ├── App Router (pages, layouts, RSC)\n    96→               ├── API Routes (/api/*)\n    97→               │    ├── Hono Router\n    98→               │    ├── Auth (Better Auth)\n    99→               │    └── Business logic services\n   100→               │\n   101→               ├── Drizzle ORM → PostgreSQL\n   102→               ├── BullMQ → Redis\n   103→               │    └── Jobs:\n   104→               │         ├── photo-analysis (→ Vision API / Ollama)\n   105→               │         ├── daily-reminder emails\n   106→               │         └── weekly summary\n   107→               └── MinIO (images)\n   108→```\n   109→\n   110→---\n   111→\n   112→## Food Database Strategy\n   113→\n   114→### Phase 1 — Seeded from open datasets\n   115→1. Import Open Food Facts (openfoodfacts.org/data) — product barcodes, branded foods\n   116→2. Import USDA FoodData Central SR Legacy — generic foods, accurate nutrition\n   117→3. Merge/deduplicate into local `foods` table\n   118→4. ~600k+ items at full import, ~50k for a curated starter set\n   119→\n   120→### Custom foods (v1)\n   121→- Users can create private custom foods (stored in their account)\n   122→- No community contribution pipeline in v1 (deferred — complexity not worth it yet)\n   123→\n   124→---\n   125→\n   126→## Photo Recognition Flow\n   127→\n   128→```\n   129→User photo → Upload to MinIO (temp)\n   130→  → BullMQ job: analyze-photo\n   131→    → Option A: Ollama (local)\n   132→         POST ollama/api/generate\n   133→         model: llava / moondream2\n   134→         prompt: \"List all food items visible. For each: name, estimated weight in grams.\"\n   135→         → parse JSON response\n   136→    → Option B: OpenAI GPT-4o Vision\n   137→         openai.chat.completions.create(...)\n   138→         → parse structured output\n   139→    → Option C: Gemini Flash (free tier)\n   140→    → Return: [{name, weightG, confidence}]\n   141→  → Look up each item in food DB\n   142→  → Return matched FoodItems to frontend\n   143→```\n   144→\n   145→Admin can configure which provider to use via env var: `VISION_PROVIDER=ollama|openai|gemini`\n   146→\n   147→---\n   148→\n   149→## Deployment Target\n   150→\n   151→Self-hosted VPS or local machine via Docker Compose. No cloud deployment targets.\n   152→\n   153→---\n   154→\n   155→## Developer Experience\n   156→\n   157→- `pnpm` monorepo (frontend + backend co-located)\n   158→- `docker compose up` → full stack locally\n   159→- Seed command: `pnpm db:seed` — loads ~10k foods, sample recipes, demo user\n   160→- OpenAPI spec generated from routes (Hono + Zod)\n   161→- E2E tests: Playwright\n   162→- Unit tests: Vitest\n   163→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bb97f10c-f3e9-4d4d-8c90-eca16b368ef0","uuid":"daf696d9-245a-46b4-987e-7660a498f067","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/claude/code/foodadvisor/spec/05-tech-stack.md","content":"# Tech Stack\n\n## Guiding Constraints\n\n- Fully open-source (MIT or compatible licenses)\n- Self-hostable via Docker Compose\n- No vendor lock-in on any critical path\n- Web-first, PWA for mobile\n- Food recognition must work without paying per-request (or have a free tier path)\n\n---\n\n## Stack Decision\n\n### Frontend\n\n| Layer | Choice | Rationale |\n|---|---|---|\n| Framework | **Next.js 15** (App Router) | SSR + RSC, great PWA support, large ecosystem |\n| Language | **TypeScript** | Type safety, especially for nutrition math |\n| Styling | **Tailwind CSS v4** | Utility-first, no runtime, good responsive |\n| Component system | **shadcn/ui** (Radix primitives) | Accessible, unstyled, own the code |\n| State management | **Zustand** | Lightweight, no boilerplate |\n| Server state / cache | **TanStack Query** | Async data fetching, offline support |\n| Charts | **Recharts** | React-native, MIT, good for health dashboards |\n| Camera / barcode | **@zxing/library** (barcode) + native `getUserMedia` | Browser-native |\n| Forms | **React Hook Form** + **Zod** | Performant, type-safe validation |\n| Offline / PWA | **Workbox** via next-pwa | Service worker, background sync |\n| Local storage | **Dexie.js** (IndexedDB wrapper) | Offline-first food log |\n\n### Backend\n\n| Layer | Choice | Rationale |\n|---|---|---|\n| Runtime | **Node.js 22 LTS** | Stable, wide hosting support |\n| Framework | **Hono** | Lightweight, edge-ready, fast, typed |\n| API style | **REST + JSON** (OpenAPI spec) | Simple, widely understood |\n| ORM | **Drizzle ORM** | TypeScript-first, lightweight, great migrations |\n| Database | **PostgreSQL 16** | Reliable, JSONB for micronutrients, full-text search |\n| Auth | **Better Auth** | Open-source, self-hosted, OAuth support |\n| File/image storage | **MinIO** (S3-compatible) | Self-hostable object storage |\n| Job queue | **BullMQ** (Redis-backed) | Background jobs: photo analysis, notifications |\n| Email | **Nodemailer** + SMTP | Password reset, self-configured |\n\n### AI / Food Recognition\n\n**Tier 1 (default): LLM Vision API**\n- Use OpenAI GPT-4o Vision or open-alternative (Ollama + LLaVA)\n- Prompt: identify food items and estimate gram weights from photo\n- Self-hosted option: Ollama with `llava` or `moondream2` model\n- Structured output: JSON list of `{name, weightG, confidence}`\n\n**Tier 2: Open Food Facts + USDA for lookup**\n- All barcode / text search backed by Open Food Facts API (free, open)\n- Fallback: USDA FoodData Central API (free API key)\n- Local DB cache: bulk import Open Food Facts dataset (CSV, ~2GB)\n\n**Voice logging**: Web Speech API (browser-native, no backend needed)\n\n**NLP quick-add**: lightweight model or LLM call to parse \"2 eggs and oatmeal 80g\"\n\n### Infrastructure (Self-hosted)\n\n```yaml\n# docker-compose.yml services\nservices:\n  app:        # Next.js (frontend + API routes)\n  postgres:   # PostgreSQL 16\n  redis:      # BullMQ + session cache\n  minio:      # Object storage (food images, user photos)\n  ollama:     # Optional: local LLM for photo recognition\n```\n\n### External APIs (all free-tier or open)\n\n| Service | Use | Cost |\n|---|---|---|\n| Open Food Facts | Barcode lookup, food DB | Free, CC BY-SA |\n| USDA FoodData Central | Food nutritional data | Free (API key) |\n| OpenAI / Anthropic | Photo recognition (optional hosted) | Pay-per-use fallback |\n| Ollama (self-hosted) | Photo recognition (fully free) | Free, own hardware |\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Diagram\n\n```\nBrowser (PWA)\n  │\n  ├── Service Worker (offline cache, background sync)\n  ├── IndexedDB (local food log, offline entries)\n  │\n  └── HTTPS → Next.js App\n               │\n               ├── App Router (pages, layouts, RSC)\n               ├── API Routes (/api/*)\n               │    ├── Hono Router\n               │    ├── Auth (Better Auth)\n               │    └── Business logic services\n               │\n               ├── Drizzle ORM → PostgreSQL\n               ├── BullMQ → Redis\n               │    └── Jobs:\n               │         ├── photo-analysis (→ Vision API / Ollama)\n               │         ├── daily-reminder emails\n               │         └── weekly summary\n               └── MinIO (images)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Food Database Strategy\n\n### Phase 1 — Seeded from open datasets\n1. Import Open Food Facts (openfoodfacts.org/data) — product barcodes, branded foods\n2. Import USDA FoodData Central SR Legacy — generic foods, accurate nutrition\n3. Merge/deduplicate into local `foods` table\n4. ~600k+ items at full import, ~50k for a curated starter set\n\n### Custom foods (v1)\n- Users can create private custom foods (stored in their account)\n- No community contribution pipeline in v1 (deferred — complexity not worth it yet)\n\n---\n\n## Photo Recognition Flow\n\n```\nUser photo → Upload to MinIO (temp)\n  → BullMQ job: analyze-photo\n    → Option A: Ollama (local)\n         POST ollama/api/generate\n         model: llava / moondream2\n         prompt: \"List all food items visible. For each: name, estimated weight in grams.\"\n         → parse JSON response\n    → Option B: OpenAI GPT-4o Vision\n         openai.chat.completions.create(...)\n         → parse structured output\n    → Option C: Gemini Flash (free tier)\n    → Return: [{name, weightG, confidence}]\n  → Look up each item in food DB\n  → Return matched FoodItems to frontend\n```\n\nAdmin can configure which provider to use via env var: `VISION_PROVIDER=ollama|openai|gemini`\n\n---\n\n## Deployment Target\n\nSelf-hosted VPS or local machine via Docker Compose. No cloud deployment targets.\n\n---\n\n## Developer Experience\n\n- `pnpm` monorepo (frontend + backend co-located)\n- `docker compose up` → full stack locally\n- Seed command: `pnpm db:seed` — loads ~10k foods, sample recipes, demo user\n- OpenAPI spec generated from routes (Hono + Zod)\n- E2E tests: Playwright\n- Unit tests: Vitest\n","numLines":163,"startLine":1,"totalLines":163}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013swfXnYckwTNS56VKbnita","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Data Models\n     2→\n     3→## Entity Relationship Diagram\n     4→\n     5→```\n     6→User\n     7→ ├── UserProfile (1:1)\n     8→ ├── DailyLog (1:N) — one per day\n     9→ │    ├── MealEntry (1:N) — foods logged\n    10→ │    ├── WaterEntry (1:N)\n    11→ │    ├── WeightEntry (0:1)\n    12→ │    └── ActivityEntry (1:N)\n    13→ ├── LessonProgress (1:N)\n    14→ └── FavoriteRecipes (1:N)\n    15→\n    16→Food (global database)\n    17→ └── FoodEntry references Food\n    18→\n    19→Recipe\n    20→ └── RecipeIngredient references Food\n    21→\n    22→Lesson (content library)\n    23→Exercise (activity library)\n    24→```\n    25→\n    26→---\n    27→\n    28→## Core Models\n    29→\n    30→### User\n    31→\n    32→```typescript\n    33→User {\n    34→  id:         uuid\n    35→  email:      string (unique)\n    36→  createdAt:  timestamp\n    37→  lastActiveAt: timestamp\n    38→}\n    39→```\n    40→\n    41→### UserProfile\n    42→\n    43→```typescript\n    44→UserProfile {\n    45→  userId:          uuid (FK → User)\n    46→\n    47→  // Demographics\n    48→  displayName:     string\n    49→  birthDate:       date\n    50→  biologicalSex:   enum(male, female, other, prefer_not_to_say)\n    51→\n    52→  // Body metrics\n    53→  currentWeightKg: decimal\n    54→  heightCm:        decimal\n    55→\n    56→  // Goals\n    57→  goal:            enum(lose_weight, maintain, build_muscle, eat_healthier)\n    58→  targetWeightKg:  decimal | null\n    59→  weeklyPaceKg:    decimal | null   // e.g. 0.5 = 0.5kg/week\n    60→  activityLevel:   enum(sedentary, light, moderate, active, very_active)\n    61→\n    62→  // Dietary\n    63→  dietaryRestrictions: string[]   // vegetarian, vegan, gluten_free, etc.\n    64→  allergies:           string[]\n    65→\n    66→  // Preferences\n    67→  units:           enum(metric, imperial)\n    68→  language:        string          // BCP-47 locale code\n    69→  timezone:        string          // IANA tz\n    70→}\n    71→```\n    72→\n    73→### DailyTargets (computed, cached)\n    74→\n    75→```typescript\n    76→DailyTargets {\n    77→  userId:       uuid\n    78→  date:         date\n    79→\n    80→  caloriesKcal: integer\n    81→  proteinG:     decimal\n    82→  carbsG:       decimal\n    83→  fatG:         decimal\n    84→  fiberG:       decimal\n    85→  waterMl:      integer\n    86→\n    87→  // Recalculated on profile change\n    88→  calculatedAt: timestamp\n    89→}\n    90→```\n    91→\n    92→---\n    93→\n    94→### Food (Database Item)\n    95→\n    96→```typescript\n    97→Food {\n    98→  id:           uuid\n    99→\n   100→  // Identity\n   101→  name:         string\n   102→  nameTranslations: Record<locale, string>\n   103→  brandName:    string | null\n   104→  barcode:      string | null       // EAN-13, UPC\n   105→\n   106→  // Source\n   107→  source:       enum(usda, open_food_facts, user_created, admin)\n   108→  sourceId:     string | null       // original DB ID\n   109→\n   110→  // Nutrition per 100g\n   111→  caloriesPer100g:  decimal\n   112→  proteinPer100g:   decimal\n   113→  carbsPer100g:     decimal\n   114→  fatPer100g:       decimal\n   115→  fiberPer100g:     decimal\n   116→  sugarPer100g:     decimal | null\n   117→  sodiumMgPer100g:  decimal | null\n   118→  saturatedFatPer100g: decimal | null\n   119→\n   120→  // Micronutrients per 100g (optional, sparse)\n   121→  micronutrients:   Record<string, decimal>  // e.g. vitamin_c_mg, iron_mg\n   122→\n   123→  // Serving sizes\n   124→  servingSizes:     ServingSize[]\n   125→  defaultServingId: uuid\n   126→\n   127→  // Meta\n   128→  category:         string | null\n   129→  imageUrl:         string | null\n   130→  verified:         boolean\n   131→  createdAt:        timestamp\n   132→}\n   133→\n   134→ServingSize {\n   135→  id:           uuid\n   136→  foodId:       uuid\n   137→  label:        string    // \"1 cup\", \"1 slice\", \"100g\"\n   138→  weightG:      decimal\n   139→}\n   140→```\n   141→\n   142→### MealEntry\n   143→\n   144→```typescript\n   145→MealEntry {\n   146→  id:           uuid\n   147→  userId:       uuid\n   148→  date:         date\n   149→  mealSlot:     enum(breakfast, morning_snack, lunch, afternoon_snack, dinner, evening_snack, other)\n   150→  loggedAt:     timestamp\n   151→\n   152→  // Food reference\n   153→  foodId:       uuid | null        // null if custom text entry\n   154→  recipeId:     uuid | null        // if logging a recipe\n   155→  customName:   string | null\n   156→\n   157→  // Quantity\n   158→  servingSizeId: uuid | null\n   159→  quantityG:    decimal            // always stored in grams\n   160→  servingLabel: string             // display label e.g. \"2 slices\"\n   161→\n   162→  // Computed snapshot (denormalized for perf)\n   163→  caloriesKcal: decimal\n   164→  proteinG:     decimal\n   165→  carbsG:       decimal\n   166→  fatG:         decimal\n   167→  fiberG:       decimal\n   168→\n   169→  // Source of entry\n   170→  source:       enum(manual, barcode, photo, voice, quick_add, recipe)\n   171→  photoUrl:     string | null\n   172→\n   173→  notes:        string | null\n   174→}\n   175→```\n   176→\n   177→### WaterEntry\n   178→\n   179→```typescript\n   180→WaterEntry {\n   181→  id:        uuid\n   182→  userId:    uuid\n   183→  date:      date\n   184→  loggedAt:  timestamp\n   185→  amountMl:  integer\n   186→}\n   187→```\n   188→\n   189→### WeightEntry\n   190→\n   191→```typescript\n   192→WeightEntry {\n   193→  id:        uuid\n   194→  userId:    uuid\n   195→  date:      date\n   196→  loggedAt:  timestamp\n   197→  weightKg:  decimal\n   198→  note:      string | null\n   199→}\n   200→```\n   201→\n   202→### ActivityEntry\n   203→\n   204→```typescript\n   205→ActivityEntry {\n   206→  id:            uuid\n   207→  userId:        uuid\n   208→  date:          date\n   209→  loggedAt:      timestamp\n   210→\n   211→  exerciseId:    uuid | null\n   212→  customName:    string | null\n   213→  durationMin:   integer\n   214→  intensityLevel: enum(low, moderate, high) | null\n   215→  caloriesBurned: decimal    // estimated\n   216→\n   217→  notes:         string | null\n   218→}\n   219→\n   220→Exercise {\n   221→  id:        uuid\n   222→  name:      string\n   223→  category:  enum(cardio, strength, flexibility, sports, daily_activity)\n   224→  metValue:  decimal    // MET for moderate intensity\n   225→  metLow:    decimal\n   226→  metHigh:   decimal\n   227→}\n   228→```\n   229→\n   230→---\n   231→\n   232→### Recipe\n   233→\n   234→```typescript\n   235→Recipe {\n   236→  id:           uuid\n   237→\n   238→  title:        string\n   239→  description:  string | null\n   240→  coverImageUrl: string | null\n   241→\n   242→  authorId:     uuid | null     // null = system recipe\n   243→  source:       enum(system, user_created)\n   244→  sourceUrl:    string | null\n   245→\n   246→  servings:     integer\n   247→  prepTimeMins: integer\n   248→  cookTimeMins: integer\n   249→  difficulty:   enum(easy, medium, hard)\n   250→\n   251→  tags:         string[]        // e.g. ['vegan', 'high_protein', 'quick']\n   252→\n   253→  ingredients:  RecipeIngredient[]\n   254→  steps:        string[]        // ordered list of step text\n   255→\n   256→  // Computed per serving\n   257→  caloriesPerServing: decimal\n   258→  proteinPerServing:  decimal\n   259→  carbsPerServing:    decimal\n   260→  fatPerServing:      decimal\n   261→  fiberPerServing:    decimal\n   262→\n   263→  published:    boolean\n   264→  createdAt:    timestamp\n   265→}\n   266→\n   267→RecipeIngredient {\n   268→  recipeId:      uuid\n   269→  foodId:        uuid\n   270→  quantityG:     decimal\n   271→  displayLabel:  string    // \"2 tbsp olive oil\"\n   272→  optional:      boolean\n   273→}\n   274→```\n   275→\n   276→---\n   277→\n   278→### Lesson (Educational Content)\n   279→\n   280→```typescript\n   281→Lesson {\n   282→  id:            uuid\n   283→  slug:          string (unique)\n   284→\n   285→  title:         string\n   286→  summary:       string\n   287→  bodyMarkdown:  string\n   288→\n   289→  category:      enum(nutrition, sleep, stress, habits, fitness, mindfulness)\n   290→  tags:          string[]\n   291→\n   292→  readTimeMin:   integer\n   293→  illustrationUrl: string | null\n   294→\n   295→  order:         integer       // sort within category\n   296→  publishedAt:   date | null\n   297→}\n   298→\n   299→LessonProgress {\n   300→  userId:        uuid\n   301→  lessonId:      uuid\n   302→  completedAt:   timestamp | null\n   303→  queuedAt:      timestamp\n   304→}\n   305→```\n   306→\n   307→---\n   308→\n   309→## Computed / Derived Values\n   310→\n   311→### Daily Summary (query, not stored)\n   312→\n   313→```typescript\n   314→DailySummary {\n   315→  date:           date\n   316→  caloriesConsumed: decimal\n   317→  caloriesBurned:   decimal\n   318→  caloriesNet:      decimal\n   319→  targetCalories:   decimal\n   320→\n   321→  proteinG:       decimal\n   322→  carbsG:         decimal\n   323→  fatG:           decimal\n   324→  fiberG:         decimal\n   325→\n   326→  waterMl:        integer\n   327→  targetWaterMl:  integer\n   328→\n   329→  weight:         decimal | null\n   330→\n   331→  mealsLogged:    integer\n   332→  activitiesLogged: integer\n   333→}\n   334→```\n   335→\n   336→### Calorie Calculation (TDEE)\n   337→\n   338→```\n   339→TDEE = BMR × ActivityMultiplier\n   340→\n   341→BMR (Mifflin-St Jeor):\n   342→  Male:   10 × weightKg + 6.25 × heightCm − 5 × age + 5\n   343→  Female: 10 × weightKg + 6.25 × heightCm − 5 × age − 161\n   344→\n   345→ActivityMultiplier:\n   346→  sedentary:    1.2\n   347→  light:        1.375\n   348→  moderate:     1.55\n   349→  active:       1.725\n   350→  very_active:  1.9\n   351→\n   352→CalorieTarget:\n   353→  maintain:      TDEE\n   354→  lose_weight:   TDEE − (weeklyPaceKg × 7700 / 7)   // 7700 kcal/kg\n   355→  build_muscle:  TDEE + (weeklyPaceKg × 7700 / 7)\n   356→\n   357→MacroSplit (defaults per WHO/DRI guidelines, user-configurable):\n   358→  protein: 0.20 × calories / 4    // g  (20% — standard, not high-protein)\n   359→  fat:     0.30 × calories / 9    // g\n   360→  carbs:   0.50 × calories / 4    // g\n   361→```\n   362→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bb97f10c-f3e9-4d4d-8c90-eca16b368ef0","uuid":"db56de2b-5cdf-478d-93cc-54a373f1243f","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/claude/code/foodadvisor/spec/02-data-models.md","content":"# Data Models\n\n## Entity Relationship Diagram\n\n```\nUser\n ├── UserProfile (1:1)\n ├── DailyLog (1:N) — one per day\n │    ├── MealEntry (1:N) — foods logged\n │    ├── WaterEntry (1:N)\n │    ├── WeightEntry (0:1)\n │    └── ActivityEntry (1:N)\n ├── LessonProgress (1:N)\n └── FavoriteRecipes (1:N)\n\nFood (global database)\n └── FoodEntry references Food\n\nRecipe\n └── RecipeIngredient references Food\n\nLesson (content library)\nExercise (activity library)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Core Models\n\n### User\n\n```typescript\nUser {\n  id:         uuid\n  email:      string (unique)\n  createdAt:  timestamp\n  lastActiveAt: timestamp\n}\n```\n\n### UserProfile\n\n```typescript\nUserProfile {\n  userId:          uuid (FK → User)\n\n  // Demographics\n  displayName:     string\n  birthDate:       date\n  biologicalSex:   enum(male, female, other, prefer_not_to_say)\n\n  // Body metrics\n  currentWeightKg: decimal\n  heightCm:        decimal\n\n  // Goals\n  goal:            enum(lose_weight, maintain, build_muscle, eat_healthier)\n  targetWeightKg:  decimal | null\n  weeklyPaceKg:    decimal | null   // e.g. 0.5 = 0.5kg/week\n  activityLevel:   enum(sedentary, light, moderate, active, very_active)\n\n  // Dietary\n  dietaryRestrictions: string[]   // vegetarian, vegan, gluten_free, etc.\n  allergies:           string[]\n\n  // Preferences\n  units:           enum(metric, imperial)\n  language:        string          // BCP-47 locale code\n  timezone:        string          // IANA tz\n}\n```\n\n### DailyTargets (computed, cached)\n\n```typescript\nDailyTargets {\n  userId:       uuid\n  date:         date\n\n  caloriesKcal: integer\n  proteinG:     decimal\n  carbsG:       decimal\n  fatG:         decimal\n  fiberG:       decimal\n  waterMl:      integer\n\n  // Recalculated on profile change\n  calculatedAt: timestamp\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Food (Database Item)\n\n```typescript\nFood {\n  id:           uuid\n\n  // Identity\n  name:         string\n  nameTranslations: Record<locale, string>\n  brandName:    string | null\n  barcode:      string | null       // EAN-13, UPC\n\n  // Source\n  source:       enum(usda, open_food_facts, user_created, admin)\n  sourceId:     string | null       // original DB ID\n\n  // Nutrition per 100g\n  caloriesPer100g:  decimal\n  proteinPer100g:   decimal\n  carbsPer100g:     decimal\n  fatPer100g:       decimal\n  fiberPer100g:     decimal\n  sugarPer100g:     decimal | null\n  sodiumMgPer100g:  decimal | null\n  saturatedFatPer100g: decimal | null\n\n  // Micronutrients per 100g (optional, sparse)\n  micronutrients:   Record<string, decimal>  // e.g. vitamin_c_mg, iron_mg\n\n  // Serving sizes\n  servingSizes:     ServingSize[]\n  defaultServingId: uuid\n\n  // Meta\n  category:         string | null\n  imageUrl:         string | null\n  verified:         boolean\n  createdAt:        timestamp\n}\n\nServingSize {\n  id:           uuid\n  foodId:       uuid\n  label:        string    // \"1 cup\", \"1 slice\", \"100g\"\n  weightG:      decimal\n}\n```\n\n### MealEntry\n\n```typescript\nMealEntry {\n  id:           uuid\n  userId:       uuid\n  date:         date\n  mealSlot:     enum(breakfast, morning_snack, lunch, afternoon_snack, dinner, evening_snack, other)\n  loggedAt:     timestamp\n\n  // Food reference\n  foodId:       uuid | null        // null if custom text entry\n  recipeId:     uuid | null        // if logging a recipe\n  customName:   string | null\n\n  // Quantity\n  servingSizeId: uuid | null\n  quantityG:    decimal            // always stored in grams\n  servingLabel: string             // display label e.g. \"2 slices\"\n\n  // Computed snapshot (denormalized for perf)\n  caloriesKcal: decimal\n  proteinG:     decimal\n  carbsG:       decimal\n  fatG:         decimal\n  fiberG:       decimal\n\n  // Source of entry\n  source:       enum(manual, barcode, photo, voice, quick_add, recipe)\n  photoUrl:     string | null\n\n  notes:        string | null\n}\n```\n\n### WaterEntry\n\n```typescript\nWaterEntry {\n  id:        uuid\n  userId:    uuid\n  date:      date\n  loggedAt:  timestamp\n  amountMl:  integer\n}\n```\n\n### WeightEntry\n\n```typescript\nWeightEntry {\n  id:        uuid\n  userId:    uuid\n  date:      date\n  loggedAt:  timestamp\n  weightKg:  decimal\n  note:      string | null\n}\n```\n\n### ActivityEntry\n\n```typescript\nActivityEntry {\n  id:            uuid\n  userId:        uuid\n  date:          date\n  loggedAt:      timestamp\n\n  exerciseId:    uuid | null\n  customName:    string | null\n  durationMin:   integer\n  intensityLevel: enum(low, moderate, high) | null\n  caloriesBurned: decimal    // estimated\n\n  notes:         string | null\n}\n\nExercise {\n  id:        uuid\n  name:      string\n  category:  enum(cardio, strength, flexibility, sports, daily_activity)\n  metValue:  decimal    // MET for moderate intensity\n  metLow:    decimal\n  metHigh:   decimal\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Recipe\n\n```typescript\nRecipe {\n  id:           uuid\n\n  title:        string\n  description:  string | null\n  coverImageUrl: string | null\n\n  authorId:     uuid | null     // null = system recipe\n  source:       enum(system, user_created)\n  sourceUrl:    string | null\n\n  servings:     integer\n  prepTimeMins: integer\n  cookTimeMins: integer\n  difficulty:   enum(easy, medium, hard)\n\n  tags:         string[]        // e.g. ['vegan', 'high_protein', 'quick']\n\n  ingredients:  RecipeIngredient[]\n  steps:        string[]        // ordered list of step text\n\n  // Computed per serving\n  caloriesPerServing: decimal\n  proteinPerServing:  decimal\n  carbsPerServing:    decimal\n  fatPerServing:      decimal\n  fiberPerServing:    decimal\n\n  published:    boolean\n  createdAt:    timestamp\n}\n\nRecipeIngredient {\n  recipeId:      uuid\n  foodId:        uuid\n  quantityG:     decimal\n  displayLabel:  string    // \"2 tbsp olive oil\"\n  optional:      boolean\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Lesson (Educational Content)\n\n```typescript\nLesson {\n  id:            uuid\n  slug:          string (unique)\n\n  title:         string\n  summary:       string\n  bodyMarkdown:  string\n\n  category:      enum(nutrition, sleep, stress, habits, fitness, mindfulness)\n  tags:          string[]\n\n  readTimeMin:   integer\n  illustrationUrl: string | null\n\n  order:         integer       // sort within category\n  publishedAt:   date | null\n}\n\nLessonProgress {\n  userId:        uuid\n  lessonId:      uuid\n  completedAt:   timestamp | null\n  queuedAt:      timestamp\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Computed / Derived Values\n\n### Daily Summary (query, not stored)\n\n```typescript\nDailySummary {\n  date:           date\n  caloriesConsumed: decimal\n  caloriesBurned:   decimal\n  caloriesNet:      decimal\n  targetCalories:   decimal\n\n  proteinG:       decimal\n  carbsG:         decimal\n  fatG:           decimal\n  fiberG:         decimal\n\n  waterMl:        integer\n  targetWaterMl:  integer\n\n  weight:         decimal | null\n\n  mealsLogged:    integer\n  activitiesLogged: integer\n}\n```\n\n### Calorie Calculation (TDEE)\n\n```\nTDEE = BMR × ActivityMultiplier\n\nBMR (Mifflin-St Jeor):\n  Male:   10 × weightKg + 6.25 × heightCm − 5 × age + 5\n  Female: 10 × weightKg + 6.25 × heightCm − 5 × age − 161\n\nActivityMultiplier:\n  sedentary:    1.2\n  light:        1.375\n  moderate:     1.55\n  active:       1.725\n  very_active:  1.9\n\nCalorieTarget:\n  maintain:      TDEE\n  lose_weight:   TDEE − (weeklyPaceKg × 7700 / 7)   // 7700 kcal/kg\n  build_muscle:  TDEE + (weeklyPaceKg × 7700 / 7)\n\nMacroSplit (defaults per WHO/DRI guidelines, user-configurable):\n  protein: 0.20 × calories / 4    // g  (20% — standard, not high-protein)\n  fat:     0.30 × calories / 9    // g\n  carbs:   0.50 × calories / 4    // g\n```\n","numLines":362,"startLine":1,"totalLines":362}}}
