{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FE74ejjWyoxfnqqQhAmeKj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The auth module initializes a database connection at module load time, causing tests to fail when there's no DATABASE_URL. I need to make the auth module lazy - don't create the DB connection until the first request.\n\nThe issue is that `auth` is initialized at module level with a DB connection. I need to make this lazy initialization. For testing, I can:\n\n1. Use lazy initialization in auth/index.ts\n2. Add DATABASE_URL to test environment via vitest.config.ts\n3. Make the auth module lazy (only connect when handler is called)\n\nThe best approach is option 3 - make auth initialization lazy. Better Auth should be initialized lazily. But since Better Auth requires the DB at init time, I need to restructure.\n\n\nActually, I think the simpler solution is to add a test DATABASE_URL to the vitest config so the module imports without throwing, then defer the actual connection until the first request. The postgres client doesn't connect immediately anyway - it only connects when you actually run a query, so I might be able to defer the initialization safely.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":83143,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1059,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bb97f10c-f3e9-4d4d-8c90-eca16b368ef0","uuid":"9720de4f-95ea-49d6-9a7d-000000000000"}
